n\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532014\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 18, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sjv1665702773431.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sjv1665702773431.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sjv1665702773431.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sjv1665702773431\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Setting DSP Widget Properties\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__setting_dsp_widget_properties_71181\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The following points explains how to setup the DSP widget properties:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__li_d9890e1_d9891e1_d9892e1\">To set the default properties of logical DSP widgets, edit the widget mappings in the [webwidgets] section of <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__li_d9893e1_d9894e1_d9895e1\">To set properties declaratively in the Uniface IDE,\n            click the More icon (<img alt=\"More icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__image_qcz_1w5_tyb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/ellipsis.png?_LANG=enus\"/>) for the property <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">DSP Widget Type Properties</span>. This is a\n            dialog in which you can set the various Uniface, HTML, and CSS properties supported by\n            the widget. To add or remove a property, select or clear the corresponding\n               checkbox.<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__note_phx_tpm_nhc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The changes are committed only when the user\n               clicks <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>; clicking <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Cancel</span> discards\n               modifications.</div><div class=\"p\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__p_d20585e1_d20586e1_d20587e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__fig_mns_nmm_nhc\">\n<img alt=\"DSP Widget Properties\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/DSP-Properties.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__image_up2_smm_nhc\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/DSP-Properties.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__li_d9896e1_d9897e1_d9898e1\">To set values of the widget properties in ProcScript,\n            use the following commands: <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__li_d9899e1_d9900e1_d9901e1\">For fields: <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$properties</span> and\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldproperties</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__li_d9902e1_d9903e1_d9904e1\">For entities:\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$entityproperties</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$curentproperties</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__li_d9905e1_d9906e1_d9907e1\">For occurrences:\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occproperties</span>\n</li>\n</ul><p class=\"p\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__p_d20588e1_d20589e1_d20590e1\">For example, to set some HTML\n            properties:</p><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">putitem/id $properties(MY_FIELD), \"html:title\" \"Hello\"\nputitem/id $properties(MY_FIELD), \"html:data-myselector\", \"Hello\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__li_d9908e1_d9909e1_d9910e1\">Once the DSP is loaded, the values of these properties can be dynamically changed in the browser using JavaScript API functions, such as <span class=\"keyword apiname\">setProperty</span> and <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getProperty</span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"owl1665702532596.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/owl1665702532596.html\" title=\"The Uniface JavaScript API is a collection of object-oriented programming interfaces that can be used in dynamic server pages (DSPs) to manipulate Uniface data objects in the browser, without round-trip processing to the server.\">APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript</a>.\n                          <div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"sjv1665702773431__note_w1578ab1b5b3b7b7_w1579ab1b5b3b7_w1580ab1b5b3_w1581ab1b5_w1582ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> In Dynamic Server Pages it is usually preferable to change the values of widget properties using JavaScript rather than ProcScript.</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532014\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532014\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Setting DSP Widget Properties Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 18, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Setting DSP Widget Properties The following points explains how to setup the DSP widget properties: To set the default properties of logical DSP widgets, edit the widget mappings in the [webwidgets] section of usys.ini . To set properties declaratively in the Uniface IDE, click the More icon ( ) for the property DSP Widget Type Properties . This is a dialog in which you can set the various Uniface, HTML, and CSS properties supported by the widget. To add or remove a property, select or clear the corresponding checkbox. Note: The changes are committed only when the user clicks OK ; clicking Cancel discards modifications. To set values of the widget properties in ProcScript, use the following commands: For fields: $properties and $fieldproperties For entities: $entityproperties and $curentproperties For occurrences: $occproperties For example, to set some HTML properties: putitem/id $properties(MY_FIELD), \"html:title\" \"Hello\" putitem/id $properties(MY_FIELD), \"html:data-myselector\", \"Hello\" Copy Once the DSP is loaded, the values of these properties can be dynamically changed in the browser using JavaScript API functions, such as setProperty and getProperty . For more information, see APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript . Tip: In Dynamic Server Pages it is usually preferable to change the values of widget properties using JavaScript rather than ProcScript. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}